uv run run_all.py start_year end_year
for example:
uv run run_all.py 2006 2026
flow: main_async_httpx.py -> stock_list_s{sy}e{ey}_unfiltered.csv
      -> empty codes written to recrawl_codes.txt -> pandas_stock.py

uv run run_all_recrawl.py start_year end_year
for example:
uv run run_all_recrawl.py 2006 2026
to re-crawl only the codes in recrawl_codes.txt (e.g. after the server
answered HTTP 200 with resultCode 500 error bodies during an outage),
merge the successful rows into stock_list_s{sy}e{ey}_unfiltered.csv
(searched in ./ then ./output), rerun pandas_stock.py there, and keep
only the still-empty codes in recrawl_codes.txt.
repeat when the crawl log shows "gave up after N resultCode-500
responses" until nothing merges; codes that stay empty with no name
are simply not supported by the site.

python3 main.py:            (sync  crawlering, time to complete:  ~24hrs)
python3 main_async_httpx.py (async crawlering, time to complete: ~1.5hrs)

to crawler all data from www.moneycome.in
output:
  -- stock_list.json
  -- stock_list.csv

pandas_stock.py: filter/sort the unfiltered CSV, also exports
stock_list_s{sy}e{ey}_unfiltered.xlsx and _filtered.xlsx sorted by
s{sy}e{ey}bao (run it from the directory holding the CSVs)

plot.py: TBD
to plot a readable animation

